{
  "stem": "4032.1",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And they defended their country, and they did a good job on the Germans, because as far as we know, in 1944, they were advancing to Poland and coming into Germany, the Russian Army.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "In the meantime, they were forming a Polish army in a place called Buzuluk.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] So I wanted desperately to get there so I can get out of-- they were saying that the Polish army is going out.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "So I was desperately wanted to get out of the country.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I went there to Buzuluk, but they didn't accept Jewish people in the Polish army.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They were saying this.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But I had a friend of mine, his brother was a doctor.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they were in desperate need of doctors, because the sicknesses were unbearable in Russia.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "All kind of dysentery and typhus and all kind of sicknesses.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So the-- he had a brother.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "His brother got a job in the office, being a Jewish man.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So I walked in in the office.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "There was a Polish officer, and I said, I would like to join the Polish army.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So he said, what's your name?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I said my name is Jacob Skovronski.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the other guy that I mentioned was sitting there.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He says, as far as I know, there were no Jewish names on the-- Jewish people under that name.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I got-- he tore off of a cigarette butt piece of paper and gave me a permit that I can go to-- to join the families of the Polish families that joined the army.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They-- they sent us to to a port city on the Caspian Sea.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It's called Krasnovodsk.",
      "word_count": 3
    }
  ],
